Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.66,0:01:51.54,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It won't take long.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.54,0:01:53.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.01,0:01:59.33,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,How did I get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.43,0:02:05.36,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias was telling me \Nabout the dragons, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.49,0:02:10.63,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Dragons?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.94,0:02:12.51,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.21,0:02:18.69,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,They've been on the move lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.69,0:02:20.40,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I've been asked to check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.31,0:02:25.70,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Here, in Iceland, is the dragons' nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.91,0:02:31.87,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,They're on the verge of \Nextinction, just like us mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.37,0:02:37.12,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,The handful of surviving breeds have been \Nrounded up here to be taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.05,0:02:46.18,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,It's remote and scarcely inhabited here, \Nwhich makes it a perfect hiding space.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.66,0:02:48.52,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Are they vicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:51.38,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,The majority of them were \Nweeded out long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.38,0:02:53.76,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,There are more docile ones now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.17,0:02:55.59,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.95,0:03:10.69,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.39,0:03:12.40,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.02,0:03:25.62,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,His half-baked talent makes him cocky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.62,0:03:27.93,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't changed much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.43,0:03:34.97,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,See, look over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.27,0:03:41.24,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The last land of the dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.38,0:04:09.22,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let her go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.29,0:04:24.10,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.08,0:04:30.36,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Does she plan to just keep sinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.01,0:04:39.36,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,My body feels heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.46,0:04:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.45,0:04:52.44,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.42,0:04:54.09,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.39,0:05:07.74,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.57,0:05:19.39,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,What an unusual guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.26,0:05:27.47,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,You smell like a mage...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.30,0:05:33.23,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,albeit a young one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.23,0:05:35.81,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,A sapling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.81,0:05:41.34,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,And you smell of plants, flowers, \Nand rocks from another place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.97,0:05:44.15,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,It's a nice scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.15,0:05:46.38,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,His eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.38,0:05:52.07,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,His whole body is like a forest of moss, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.30,0:05:56.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,He's a breed of dragon called an uil.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.83,0:06:01.99,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,He's both father and the mother to the forest, \Nbearing vegetation on his decaying body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.16,0:06:05.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Apologies for the rough handling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.12,0:06:08.59,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the land of \Ndragons, Daughter of Thorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.21,0:06:11.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:14.79,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,There was commotion among the ariels.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.79,0:06:17.74,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,They said that Thorn had\Nfinally taken an apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.20,0:06:21.18,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,For them, rumors spread \Nliterally like the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.83,0:06:24.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You arrived quite quickly this time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.38,0:06:29.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,When are you going to stop hiding \Nin your apprentice's shadows, Thorn?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.46,0:06:31.82,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, Ainsworth?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.61,0:06:47.97,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,When the old fogey finishes his bumbling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.53,0:06:54.20,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,It's been 300 years, and you still haven't\N stopped toying with people, have you, Echos?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.75,0:06:59.60,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want your apprentice \Nto freeze to death, Ainsworth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.94,0:07:07.72,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.66,0:07:13.19,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You're absolutely soaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.01,0:07:16.51,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Nettles in the shadow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.94,0:07:21.15,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Ring of holly...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.61,0:07:31.85,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.85,0:07:34.46,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.91,0:07:37.55,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,What are you grinning at?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:43.18,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,At this little brat acting \Nlike he's all grown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:44.43,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Shut it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.89,0:07:53.36,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, that's Lindel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.36,0:07:57.67,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,He's a mage, like me, and \Ncaretaker of this dragon's nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.97,0:07:59.03,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Caretaker?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.48,0:08:03.99,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,His duty is to keep the land of dragons \Nhidden from the sight of ordinary humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:05.72,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Hence, "caretaker."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.41,0:08:11.52,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Despite his appearance, he's a mischievous \Nsenior, even more ancient than I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.52,0:08:12.58,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,so be careful around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.43,0:08:14.34,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.64,0:08:15.88,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.88,0:08:17.36,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Are you done talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.36,0:08:18.09,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.23,0:08:20.33,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play! Let's play!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.33,0:08:21.78,Magus-top,B,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.74,0:08:23.77,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Those are dragon hatchlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.78,0:08:23.77,Magus-top,B,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:24.65,Magus-top,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.65,0:08:26.00,Magus-top,,0000,0000,0000,,Please?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.65,0:08:26.59,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,The one with wings is a gwee.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.41,0:08:27.68,Magus-top,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.59,0:08:28.49,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,The one by your feet is a beana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.15,0:08:31.23,Magus-top,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's play!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.49,0:08:31.23,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,The slow-moving one is an uil.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.81,0:08:35.15,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Granted, that's just what \NI call them personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.28,0:08:33.66,Magus-top,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:35.48,Magus-top,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.48,0:08:37.17,Magus-top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.28,0:08:37.32,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.17,0:08:38.28,Magus-top,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.61,0:08:42.33,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, has there been any trouble lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.67,0:08:46.68,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,They're making a fuss again, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.68,0:08:48.59,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Food has been scarce this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.59,0:08:50.89,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,A number of the dragons\N have been traveling far.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.25,0:09:00.64,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, would you mind \Nplaying with them for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.93,0:09:14.36,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.36,0:09:15.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.09,0:09:20.77,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Let's jump off and practice \Ngliding toward the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.53,0:09:29.30,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Humans can fly these days, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.30,0:09:34.01,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Er, that might be hard without having my bones\Nand muscles modified at the genetic level.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.49,0:09:44.21,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.42,0:09:53.31,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,And now I'm wet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:56.08,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, can we try that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.88,0:09:56.64,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,That was awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.27,0:10:46.95,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He has wings, so I guess \Nhe must be able to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.43,0:10:49.83,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He's all tattered, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.02,0:11:00.19,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Have you never seen a dragon before?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.19,0:11:01.58,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry, I didn't mean to...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.01,0:11:06.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.78,0:11:08.79,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Nevin's awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.79,0:11:11.75,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's won't be long before I return home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.75,0:11:15.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'd supposed you would prefer to watch \Nover the rollicking young instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.78,0:11:18.61,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.61,0:11:19.90,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,His time?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.90,0:11:23.46,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Nevin's turning into a tree soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.46,0:11:24.86,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.86,0:11:27.59,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,All the uils do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.59,0:11:30.52,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,They turn into excellent trees and pasture.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.40,0:11:49.01,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,When you say "return"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.08,0:11:51.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:06.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to turn into trees and \Nmoss and boulders when we die, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.78,0:12:08.24,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.24,0:12:09.87,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,When you die?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.56,0:12:14.99,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We don't fear death the way you humans do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.52,0:12:20.68,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We live our lives to the fullest, so \Nthat we're never left with regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.82,0:12:38.29,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.86,0:12:43.80,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're a kind-hearted child.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.57,0:12:48.95,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We understand that what \Nis given to us is the same
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.95,0:12:54.08,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,as what is given to all \Nwho live on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.47,0:13:01.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Whether that's the joy or the pain of \Nliving, or the sadness or loneliness of dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.25,0:13:05.50,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I've lived for \Nmore than enough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.96,0:13:11.22,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,For a long, long time, even for a dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.79,0:13:15.70,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Life will be handed down \Nto the next generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.16,0:13:19.06,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You have no reason to grieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.79,0:13:20.77,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.24,0:13:25.77,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not grieving.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.50,0:13:28.53,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.28,0:13:33.42,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's really...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.76,0:14:00.14,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The living shouldn't envy the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.93,0:14:04.64,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot fly, so it's\Nfortunate that you didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.57,0:14:12.86,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't have known who to take as \Nhis apprentice if he hadn't met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.66,0:14:16.76,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Were you going through my memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.45,0:14:21.15,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That was a disrespectful \Nthing to do to a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.15,0:14:22.49,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.77,0:14:33.79,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I believe I ought to let you experience the \Njoy of true flight, as you cannot fly yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.18,0:14:42.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have the strength to fly anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.81,0:14:48.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,but I can show you the sky I see in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.25,0:14:51.06,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Behold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.30,0:16:50.63,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Nevin is having his \Nfinal dream, along with Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.56,0:16:55.34,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of dragons are passing the torch lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.34,0:16:57.96,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose he's the last of the old dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.43,0:17:01.24,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same for dragons as \Nit is for magic, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.56,0:17:05.28,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,We're being pushed aside by the changing \Ntimes and the growing number of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.70,0:17:10.28,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,If Chise becomes a mage, she may \Nvery well be of the last generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.16,0:17:12.75,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Does that bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.42,0:17:20.06,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Chise's power is flowing into Nevin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.76,0:17:24.01,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,She'll be a great help to Nevin,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.01,0:17:29.23,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,but a Sleigh Beggy's overwhelming \Npower, at times, hurts its wielder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.29,0:17:32.92,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't know how to hold back yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.85,0:17:36.81,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it your job to teach her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.44,0:17:43.41,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,She won't last three years \Nunless you stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.41,0:17:44.54,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.54,0:17:46.37,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let her out of your sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.90,0:17:49.74,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,There are countless people \Nwho want a Sleigh Beggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.23,0:17:52.67,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,The rumors these days aren't encouraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.91,0:17:55.46,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,She wasn't easy to obtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.46,0:17:58.17,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let her go that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.06,0:18:05.53,Magus-internal/narrator,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,I hope she grows up safely...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.42,0:18:09.49,Magus-internal/narrator,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,That Sleigh Beggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.37,0:18:16.35,Default,Nevin,0000,0000,0000,,Our kind abandoned the skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.76,0:18:20.23,Default,Nevin,0000,0000,0000,,But it was always our fate\Nto dwell beneath it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.32,0:18:24.72,Default,Nevin,0000,0000,0000,,Your name has the character\N for "bird" within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.72,0:18:28.46,Default,Nevin,0000,0000,0000,,You must also fly beneath \Nthis sky, in order to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.47,0:18:31.92,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,In order to live?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.06,0:18:38.97,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.56,0:18:50.33,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,In order to live...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.24,0:18:58.94,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:00.96,Default,Nevin,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.43,0:19:06.28,Default,Nevin,0000,0000,0000,,Because you were here, I spent \Nmy last moments in flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.22,0:19:08.66,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.83,0:19:19.25,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,A little while ago, Lindel \Nplanted a small seed in my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.38,0:19:32.36,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,It'll produce beautiful \Nwhite flowers, I'm told.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.23,0:19:37.78,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,You're a mage, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:42.04,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,You'll need a wand, someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.57,0:19:46.73,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Make one out of my branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.98,0:19:57.15,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, little mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.57,0:20:02.42,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle was awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.42,0:20:03.58,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.58,0:20:06.67,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can become a huge tree, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.90,0:20:14.75,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.46,0:20:18.98,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Was it beautiful in Nevin's sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.04,0:20:22.99,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It was very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.86,0:20:26.28,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That was a rare thing you got to witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.87,0:20:30.85,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Not many get to witness\N a dragon return to the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.89,0:20:34.66,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Lindenbaum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:38.00,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Its beautiful white flowers are in bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.70,0:20:46.46,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,There's not a single reason to be sad, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.28,0:20:48.96,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,This is the work of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:55.22,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,The dragons all spend enormous \Ntime strengthening their minds,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.73,0:21:01.40,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,and in the end, are at peace with \Nbecoming seedbeds for other life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.05,0:21:09.82,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.87,0:21:12.66,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Like Nevin said,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.66,0:21:16.79,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,we'll return for a branch to use for your wand, \Nonce it's time for you to have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.40,0:21:21.42,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Our business here is done for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.42,0:21:22.84,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.84,0:21:25.52,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,What? Leaving so soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.52,0:21:28.87,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the only matter \NI've had shoved at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.87,0:21:30.77,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,You could just bail on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.32,0:21:33.89,Default,Lindel,0000,0000,0000,,You're surprisingly proper, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.89,0:21:35.10,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.00,0:21:41.86,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,This is nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.83,0:21:44.49,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.23,0:21:48.49,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.14,0:21:54.42,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He was just like a stranger who happened \Nto show me some kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.49,0:22:02.67,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,My head's spinning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.41,0:22:07.17,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because of the flight?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.59,0:22:11.18,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But still,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.85,0:22:16.18,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help but be a little envious
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.37,0:22:22.89,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,of the peaceful way he passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.64,0:23:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Past the tunnel was\Na nation of cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.23,0:24:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, in a land drowning in sadness,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.70,0:24:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the girl learns of her own cruel duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.12,0:24:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, help us. Help me.
